### Type Scale System

#### Modular Scale
- ‚úÖ **Use consistent ratio**: 1.2 (Minor Third), 1.25 (Major Third), 1.333 (Perfect Fourth), 1.5 (Perfect Fifth)
- ‚úÖ **Define complete scale**: From smallest to largest
- ‚úÖ **Use CSS variables**: For easy maintenance
- ‚úÖ **Test on actual devices**: Ensure sizes work in context

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Modular scale with 1.25 ratio (Major Third) */
:root {
  /* Base size */
  --text-base: 1rem;           /* 16px */
  
  /* Scale down (√∑ 1.25) */
  --text-sm: 0.8rem;           /* 12.8px */
  --text-xs: 0.64rem;          /* 10.24px */
  
  /* Scale up (√ó 1.25) */
  --text-lg: 1.25rem;          /* 20px */
  --text-xl: 1.563rem;         /* 25px */
  --text-2xl: 1.953rem;        /* 31.25px */
  --text-3xl: 2.441rem;        /* 39.06px */
  --text-4xl: 3.052rem;        /* 48.83px */
  --text-5xl: 3.815rem;        /* 61.04px */
}

/* Application to elements */
h1 { font-size: var(--text-5xl); }
h2 { font-size: var(--text-4xl); }
h3 { font-size: var(--text-3xl); }
h4 { font-size: var(--text-2xl); }
h5 { font-size: var(--text-xl); }
h6 { font-size: var(--text-lg); }

p, li { font-size: var(--text-base); }
small { font-size: var(--text-sm); }
.caption { font-size: var(--text-xs); }
```

#### Fluid Typography with clamp()
- ‚úÖ **Scale smoothly between breakpoints**
- ‚úÖ **Use clamp() for automatic scaling**
- ‚úÖ **Define min, preferred, and max sizes**
- ‚úÖ **Test at various screen widths**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Fluid typography that scales with viewport */
:root {
  /* clamp(min, preferred, max) */
  --text-sm: clamp(0.875rem, 0.85rem + 0.125vw, 1rem);
  --text-base: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.25vw, 1.125rem);
  --text-lg: clamp(1.125rem, 1.05rem + 0.375vw, 1.5rem);
  --text-xl: clamp(1.25rem, 1.1rem + 0.75vw, 2rem);
  --text-2xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.3rem + 1vw, 2.5rem);
  --text-3xl: clamp(1.875rem, 1.5rem + 1.875vw, 3.5rem);
  --text-4xl: clamp(2.25rem, 1.75rem + 2.5vw, 4.5rem);
  --text-5xl: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 5vw, 6rem);
}

/* Headings scale automatically with viewport */
h1 {
  font-size: var(--text-5xl);
  /* On mobile (375px): ~3rem (48px)
     On desktop (1440px): ~6rem (96px) */
}

h2 {
  font-size: var(--text-4xl);
  /* On mobile: ~2.25rem (36px)
     On desktop: ~4.5rem (72px) */
}

body {
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  /* On mobile: ~1rem (16px)
     On desktop: ~1.125rem (18px) */
}
```

### Line Height and Spacing

#### Line Height Guidelines
- ‚úÖ **Body text: 1.5-1.75** for comfortable reading
- ‚úÖ **Headings: 1.1-1.3** for tighter, impactful spacing
- ‚úÖ **Small text: 1.4-1.6** for clarity
- ‚úÖ **Adjust with font size**: Larger text = tighter leading

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Line height system */
:root {
  --leading-none: 1;
  --leading-tight: 1.25;
  --leading-snug: 1.375;
  --leading-normal: 1.5;
  --leading-relaxed: 1.625;
  --leading-loose: 2;
}

/* Headings: Tight line height for impact */
h1, h2, h3 {
  line-height: var(--leading-tight);
}

/* Body: Comfortable reading */
p, li {
  line-height: var(--leading-normal);
}

/* Long-form content: More relaxed */
article p {
  line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
}

/* Small text: Slightly tighter but still readable */
small, .caption {
  line-height: var(--leading-snug);
}

/* Code: Monospace needs more space */
code, pre {
  line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
}
```

#### Letter Spacing (Tracking)
- ‚úÖ **Uppercase: increase spacing (+0.05-0.1em)**
- ‚úÖ **Small text: slight increase (+0.01-0.02em)**
- ‚úÖ **Large headings: slight decrease (-0.01-0.02em)**
- ‚úÖ **Body text: usually default (0)**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Letter spacing adjustments */
:root {
  --tracking-tighter: -0.05em;
  --tracking-tight: -0.025em;
  --tracking-normal: 0;
  --tracking-wide: 0.025em;
  --tracking-wider: 0.05em;
  --tracking-widest: 0.1em;
}

/* Large headings: Slightly tighter */
h1, h2 {
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
}

/* Uppercase text: More spacing */
.uppercase {
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
}

/* Small labels: Slightly more space */
label, .label {
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* Body text: Default spacing */
p {
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-normal);
}
```

### Line Length and Measure

#### Optimal Line Length
- ‚úÖ **50-75 characters per line** (65ch optimal)
- ‚úÖ **Use `ch` unit** for character-based width
- ‚úÖ **Narrower for mobile** (45-60 characters)
- ‚úÖ **Consider reading context**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Optimal line length for readability */
.prose {
  max-width: 65ch;              /* ~65 characters per line */
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

/* Wider for short-form content */
.card-text {
  max-width: 45ch;              /* Shorter for cards */
}

/* Even wider for short headlines */
.headline {
  max-width: 20ch;              /* Short, impactful lines */
}

/* Full-width for certain contexts */
.code-block {
  max-width: 100%;              /* Code needs horizontal space */
  overflow-x: auto;
}

/* Responsive line length */
.article-body {
  max-width: min(65ch, 90vw);   /* 65ch or 90% viewport, whichever is smaller */
  padding: 0 1rem;
}
```

### Font Loading and Performance

#### Modern Font Loading
- ‚úÖ **Use `font-display: swap`** for faster perceived load
- ‚úÖ **Preload critical fonts**
- ‚úÖ **Subset fonts** to reduce file size
- ‚úÖ **Consider variable fonts** for flexibility with one file

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Preload critical fonts -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>

<!-- Preload the most critical font -->
<link rel="preload" 
      href="/fonts/inter-var.woff2" 
      as="font" 
      type="font/woff2" 
      crossorigin>

<!-- Load fonts with font-display: swap -->
<style>
  @font-face {
    font-family: 'Inter';
    src: url('/fonts/inter-var.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 100 900;           /* Variable font weight range */
    font-display: swap;             /* Show fallback immediately */
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>
```

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Font loading with fallback system */
:root {
  --font-primary: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
}

body {
  font-family: var(--font-primary);
  font-weight: 400;
  /* Browser shows system font immediately, swaps when Inter loads */
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Limit font weights loaded */
/* Only load weights you actually use */
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap');

/* ‚ùå Bad: Loading all weights */
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@100;200;300;400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap');
```

#### Variable Fonts
- ‚úÖ **One file, multiple weights/styles**
- ‚úÖ **Better performance than multiple files**
- ‚úÖ **Smooth interpolation between weights**
- ‚úÖ **Growing browser support**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Variable font usage */
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  src: url('/fonts/Inter-VariableFont.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 100 900;           /* Supports any weight in this range */
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

h1 {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  font-weight: 750;               /* Can use any value between 100-900 */
}

h2 {
  font-weight: 650;
}

p {
  font-weight: 400;
}

strong {
  font-weight: 600;
}
```

