## üìù Key Points

### Must Have
- Readable body text size (16px minimum)
- Optimal line length (50-75 characters)
- Comfortable line height (1.5+ for body)
- Clear heading hierarchy
- Performance-optimized font loading
- Responsive typography scaling

### Do
- Use modular type scale with consistent ratios
- Limit to 2-3 font families maximum
- Use clamp() for fluid typography
- Preload critical fonts
- Use font-display: swap
- Test readability on actual devices
- Maintain 65ch max width for body text
- Use relative units (rem, em) for scalability

### Don't
- Don't use less than 16px for body text on mobile
- Don't load all font weights unnecessarily
- Don't use more than 3 font families
- Don't ignore line length (no full-width text)
- Don't use tight line-height for body text
- Don't use random font sizes
- Don't make headings too similar in size
- Don't sacrifice readability for aesthetics

